entries.femaleVariant: A tortoise?! Is this some kinda joke?
Barry's not OK.
Aren't you going a little overboard?
Barry's not OK. I mean, if that tortoise was the one thing that got him up in the morning...
Aren't you goin' a little overboard? He had a bond, I get that, but does that mean you gotta dive straight down the rabbit-hole?
You can ignore the facts all you want – doesn't mean the problem's just gonna up and disappear.
I don't know about you, but Barry didn't seem like the kinda pig to crack jokes.
Now you're starting to get it.
His friends have to know. Hopefully it's not too late.
If I were you, I'd tell his pals. People've done dumber things over less than a dead tortoise.
But a tortoise...? It makes no sense, Johnny! Barry said he was the only person he could spill his guts to...
That not a good enough reason to buy a niche in a wall – pay a visit from time to time?
You know how it goes. Stare too long into the abyss, the abyss'll stare right back atcha.
Takin' a step into it wouldn't be so drastic – considerin' the shit he's seen in his lifetime.
It ain't normal.
You're right...
Gonk blew eddies lookin' after an expensive-ass tortoise... just so he could talk to it?
Ahh, you're right... I sound like an asshole.
entries.maleVariant: You're right... I sound like an asshole.

entries.femaleVariant: Picture this – you've got no one. Beloved granny's been in the ground for years. Only thing she left behind's a dumb-fucking tortoise.
That sound normal to you?
Guy was depressed as shit – only friends he had wouldn't listen. What the fuck else was he s'posed to do?
But when grandma told ya about life, that tortoise was there. When that same life kicked ya in the nads, when poor grams croaked, it was right there.
Imagine how alone you've gotta be to buy a niche for a goddamn animal.
You think it's that bad...?
Shit, Barry needs help.
A tortoise? Is this a joke?
